  "prompt": "What are some visible signs of pregnancy?",
  "response": "Visible signs of pregnancy can vary widely among individuals, but some common physical signs include:\n\n1. **Bumps or Belly Growth**: As the pregnancy progresses, the abdomen will begin to bulge as the uterus expands.\n\n2. **Breast Changes**: Breasts may become larger, fuller, and more tender. Darkening of the areolas and visible veins can also occur.\n\n3. **Skin Changes**: Some women may experience a \"pregnancy glow,\" while others may develop dark patches on the skin (melasma) or a linea nigra (a dark line that runs from the navel to the pubic bone).\n\n4. **Weight Gain**: Gradual weight gain is typical in pregnancy as the body supports the developing fetus.\n\n5. **Swelling**: Some pregnant women may experience swelling in the feet, ankles, and hands, particularly in the later stages of pregnancy.\n\n6. **Changes in Posture**: As the belly grows, some women may exhibit changes in posture as they adjust to the weight of the baby.\n\n7. **Fatigue**: While not always a visible sign, extreme fatigue can be noted by others, particularly in the first and third trimesters.\n\n8. **Clothing Changes**: Many women may switch to looser clothing or maternity wear as their bodies change.\n\nIt's important to note that some of these signs can also be caused by factors other than pregnancy, and not everyone will exhibit all of these signs. A positive pregnancy test is the most reliable way to confirm pregnancy.",
